FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - ISRAEL (02): OIE
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 6 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE WAHID Information, Foot & Mouth Disease, Israel - Follow-up No.
1 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=4391>

Summary: Report type Follow-up report No. 1
Start date 28 Dec 2006
Date of confirmation of event 1 Jan 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of listed disease
Date of previous occurrence December 2005
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent FMD virus: Serotype O
Nature of diagnosis Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory
(advanced), Necropsy
Report pertains to Entire country
Related reports: Immediate notification 2 Jan 2007), Follow-up report No.
1, 4 Jan 2007)
New Outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (MEVO HAMMA) MEVO HAMMA, Golan, HAZAFON
Date of start of outbreak 1 Jan 2007
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species Cattle
Susceptible 210
Cases 15
Deaths 5
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected population: The herd contains calves aged 1-8 months. The
affected calves are 1-3 months old and have not yet been vaccinated. The
older calves are not affected due to previous vaccination. The sick calves
show classical signs of the disease such as limping, ulcers in the mucosa
of the mouth and the tongue and high fever.
Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics:
Apparent morbidity rate 7.14 percent
Apparent mortality rate 2.38 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 33.33 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 2.38 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death, destruction
or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
Measures already applied: Movement control inside the country, Vaccination
in response to the outbreak (s), Quarantine, Vaccination permitted, No
treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: Screening
Laboratory name and type: National FMD Laboratory, Kimron Veterinary
Institute (National laboratory)
Species: Goats
Test: antigen (Ag) detection ELISA
Test date: 1 Jan 2007
Result: Positive
----
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[For pictures of FMD lesions in the affected calves at Mevo Hamma, see page
3 at
<http://www.vetserv.moag.gov.il/NR/rdonlyres/FF40AA4E-10BC-441D-9FA6-EF9159661F29/1430/hozerpevetlafaim4108.pdf>.
The WAHID system report also provides a map showing the outbreak location
near the Israeli borders with Jordan and with Syria. Further useful
location information and maps can be found referenced in the comment of
Mod.AS in Foot & mouth disease, bovine - Israel 20070104.0042.
It is important to note that the test data provided refer to the original
test in goats. The tests results for this outbreak in cattle have not yet
been provided. See Foot & mouth disease, caprine - Israel (02): OIE
20070103.0021 for the original test results. - Mod.PC]
